-- Gujarat State Electricity Seeks 1 Million Tons of Imported Coal
-- B y   D i n a k a r   S e t h u r a m a n
-- 2012-08-10T08:58:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-10/gujarat-state-electricity-seeks-1-million-tons-of-imported-coal.html
Gujarat State Electricity Corp. is
seeking one million metric tons of imported thermal coal,
according to a document on its  website .  The state-owned utility in western  India  is seeking power-
plant coal of 5,800 kilocalories per kilogram as received basis,
according to the document. The tender is for fuel with moisture
of 16 percent, ash of 12 percent and sulfur of 0.6 percent,
delivered over 12 months at Dahej, Magdalla, Mundra or Navlakhi.
The tender closes Aug. 23.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dinakar Sethuraman in  Singapore  at 
